                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> ORMESBY (Priory of). Charter (indented) by which the <orgName key="org_108074">prior and convent of Ormesby</orgName>,
               in 1243 agree with the prior of <orgName role="prior" key="org_108078">Rovenham</orgName>, concerning the 
               gift of certain lands in <placeName key="place_1083518">Rovenhamnsis (?Cavenham)</placeName> by
               <persName>
                           <forename>Clement</forename> 
                           <surname>Flandre</surname>
                        </persName> to the
               said priory of Ormesby,
               viz. that the said prior of Rovenham quit-claims all right in the said lands, and the
               prior and convent of Ormesby agree to pay to the prior of Rovenham annually 2d, and 
               3d, and a half-pennyworth of incense to the church of St. Mary of Rovenham.
                </p>
                  </msItem>
